===Etymology===
Old English ''[[wir#Old English|wīr]]'' < Proto-Germanic ''*wiraz'' < Proto-Indo-European ''*wei-'' ('to turn,' 'to twist,' 'to plait'). Cognate with Swedish [[vira]] ('to twist'), Latin ''vieo, [[viere]]'' ('to weave together'), Welsh [[gwyr]] ('bent'), and Greek [[ίρις]] ('rainbow').

